(4)
All liabilities of each corporation or eligible entity that is merged into
the survivor are vested in the survivor;

(5) The name of the survivor may, but need not be,
substituted in any pending proceeding for the name of any party to the merger
whose separate existence ceased in the merger;

(6) The articles of incorporation or
organic documents of the survivor are amended to the extent provided in the
plan of merger;
